## Product & Architecture Requirements Document (PRD/ARD)## Project Code Name: ReviewPilot (v1.0)
------------------------------
## 1. Executive Summary & Problem Space## 1.1 The Core Problem
Performance reviews are structurally broken for both employees and managers due to three distinct cognitive friction points:

* Recency Bias: Evaluations favor the last 30–60 days of the cycle. Major accomplishments from earlier months are routinely forgotten.
* Translation Friction: Converting raw engineering output (e.g., bug fixes, code refactoring) into high-impact corporate/HR business language is time-consuming and unnatural for developers.
* Aggregation Fatigue: Managers managing 5 to 15 direct reports struggle to track, remember, and objectively score peer metrics against custom HR rubrics at the end of the financial year.

## 1.2 Target Audience

* Primary User (IC): Individual software engineers, product owners, and business analysts looking to secure optimal, accurate ratings.
* Secondary User (Manager): Engineering leads and managers seeking an automated ledger to continuously track peer progress and generate objective feedback.

