## 5. Security, Risk, & Compliance Guardrails

* Model Zero-Retention: All API handshakes with foundational models via Amazon Bedrock are executed under explicit opt-out terms ensuring zero prompt logging, zero context retention, and zero exposure to fine-tuning pipelines.
* Data at Rest & Motion Isolation: All logs are encrypted using envelope encryption via AWS KMS keys unique to the specific user/tenant.
* Manager Data Access Restrictions: A strict Role-Based access fence prevents managers from seeing an employee's private daily journal reflection unless the employee explicitly flags an entry as "Shared with Manager for Review Alignment."

